snippet.textDisplay:
Great work mate.

Can I just say to any Aussie reading this; if you are wanting to help and do something beyond giving to the RFS/CFA charity efforts, here's how you can help. Look at the bushfire map, find the towns affected and call their local fire station. Ask for their BSB and account number and deposit your donation directly, this will be received in full and immediately for them to use. Also ask them if they need supplies and if so, get some mates together and crowd-donate what is needed. We did this for Numeralla and it provided weeks worth of relief for the town.
